Here's a simplified version of the relevant section:

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Starting multimedia blog...");
        // initializing modules
        MediaModule media = new MediaModule()
        media.initialize();
    }
}

I suspect the missing semicolon after 'new MediaModule()' might be the issue, but I'm wondering if there's anything else I should be looking out for, especially with the new interactive features I'm adding.

You're correct—the missing semicolon after the instantiation of MediaModule is likely the culprit here. The corrected code should be:

MediaModule media = new MediaModule();

Additionally, ensure that any new interactive or multimedia components you add have the proper initialization and that all dependencies and method calls are correctly referenced. It might also help to use an IDE that can highlight such syntax errors in real-time.
